<p>Further to the southwest is the small plain of Phan Rang, surrounded by high mountains. The entire Nui Chua-Phan Rang area almost forms a basin terrain, separated in the north, west and south by mountain blocks with terrain heights of over 500m to over 1000m. The north and south ends are blocked by mountain blocks spreading to the sea with an average altitude of 500-700m.</p>




